{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/how-to-create-a-snippet-in-visual-studio-code/","webpackCompilationHash":"","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Here's how you make a custom, global snippet in VSCode.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Press <kbd>COMMAND</kbd> + <kbd>SHIFT</kbd> + <kbd>P</kbd> to open the command palette.</li>\n<li>Find \"Preferences: Configure User Snippets\".</li>\n<li>Click \"New Global snippets file\". This will open up a file with a <code class=\"language-text\">.code-snippets</code> extension in <code class=\"language-text\">~/Library/Application Support/Code/User/snippets/filename.code-snippets</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I made one that will allow me to type <code class=\"language-text\">perr</code> + TAB to print forced PHP errors.</p>\n<div class=\"filename\">PHPErrors.code-snippets</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"token string\">\"Show PHP Errors\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token string\">\"scope\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"php\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token string\">\"prefix\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"perr\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token string\">\"body\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"token string\">\"ini_set('display_errors', 1); ini_set('display_startup_errors', 1); error_reporting(E_ALL);\"</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token string\">\"description\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Show PHP Errors\"</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>And that's all.</p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Here's how you make a custom, global snippet in VSCode. Press COMMAND + SHIFT + P to open the command palette. Find \"Preferences: Configureâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"How to Create a Snippet in Visual Studio Code","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":150,"height":150,"src":"/static/43b0e32dbc26e7a02506a5c6aabd8d7a/4148e/vsc.png","srcSet":"/static/43b0e32dbc26e7a02506a5c6aabd8d7a/4148e/vsc.png 1x"}}},"slug":"how-to-create-a-snippet-in-visual-studio-code","date":"2018-06-12T00:00:00.000Z","categories":["Tools"],"tags":["php","setup"],"template":"post"},"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-create-a-snippet-in-visual-studio-code/","date":"2018-06-12T00:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/how-to-create-a-snippet-in-visual-studio-code/"}}}